  * New upstream release (v1.6.0):
    - `am` strips extra paths from pull request URLs

 -- Sebastian Boehm <sebastian@sometimesfood.org>  Wed, 30 Mar 2011 00:17:26 +0200

hub (1.5.1-1) lucid; urgency=low

  * New upstream release (v1.5.1):
    - Support git aliases
    - Gracefully handle HTTP errors in `create` and `fork`
    - Support Gist URLs in `hub am`
  * Add debian/rules targets for merging upstream and packaging

 -- Sebastian Boehm <sebastian@sometimesfood.org>  Sat, 19 Mar 2011 16:53:46 +0100

hub (1.5.0-1) lucid; urgency=low

  * New upstream release (v1.5.0):
    - Support multiple URLs for a single remote
    - Support for GITHUB_USER and GITHUB_TOKEN env variables
    - Add ability to cherry-pick pull requests and commits with `hub am`
    - Use HTTPS for GitHub URLs (browse/compare/cherry-pick)

 -- Sebastian Boehm <sebastian@sometimesfood.org>  Wed, 29 Dec 2010 01:26:17 +0100

